history.content:
Please show your history of workload when asking if something is doable. Some people can take 6 difficult classes all at once, and some can only take 1 tech a semester. As such it is impossible to answer.

You should take this combination in the spring as Shewchuck's 189 is ~ 1.5x CS170 workload, 1x level of difficulty. I would say 127 topics are the same difficulty as 170 if you have the requisite strong linear algebra background, and math maturity. It has about 1/2x workload, but effectively 1.5x difficulty because you have to self learn many things in the class. I would put this class on level of EE126 if your linear algebra is weak. CS164 is very high workload, I haven't taken it before.

As title. I heard many suggestions that 189+164 taken together is doable, I also heard 189+127 is very meaningful (complementing each other). I'd to ask is taking them all together doable? Thanks !

Also, I heard that 

184  160  169

these three courses are not that useful in some sense, but it seems these 3 courses provide some projects that can be put on resume. Could anyone who has taken them give some "usefulness" feedbacks? Thank you all so much!
